cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CR 

This paper discusses bibliometric indicators and their application in measuring the citation impact of academic authors. It is likely to be categorized under cs.DL (Digital Libraries) as it deals with the analysis of scholarly publications and their impact. It may also be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it discusses the measurement of citation impact. Additionally, it may be relevant to cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it discusses the use of bibliometric indicators in academic evaluation. It may also be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it discusses the ranking of academic authors. Finally, it may be relevant to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it discusses the degree of distinction between analytical units.
